Parliament, Friday, 20 April 2018 – The Portfolio Committee on Social Development is saddened by the passing of the struggle stalwart, Dr Zola Skweyiya. Dr Skweyiya who became the Minister of Public Services and Administration in 1994 and then the Minister of Social Development in 1999, will be remembered not only for his contribution to the struggle for freedom, but the role he played in establishing the Centre for Development Studies and the South African Legal Defence Fund among other things. The committee Chairperson, Ms Rosemary Capa said: “the passing of Dr Skweyiya, whose legacy will continue to live on, is an enormous loss to South Africa” The Committee wishes to express its heartfelt condolences to the family, friends and colleagues of Dr Skweyiya. ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON SOCIAL DEVELOPMENT, MS ROSEMARY CAPA For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s media officer: Name: Felicia Lombard
